  "text": "DNA extraction, purification, and quantitation. Soil DNA was extracted from each of the 0.5-g soil samples using the MO BIO PowerSoil ® DNA isolation kit (MO BIO Laboratories, Carlsbad, CA, USA) according to the manufacturer's protocol. Soil DNA was extracted by freeze-grinding mechanical lysis as described previously [CITATION_1] . The freshly extracted DNA was purified twice using 0.5% low melting point agarose gels, followed by phenol-chloroform-butanol extraction. DNA quality was assessed using 260 nm/280 nm and 260 nm/230 nm ratios, and final DNA concentrations were quantified by the PicoGreen method using a FLUOstar Optima microplate reader (BMG Labtech, Jena, Germany).",
